# Project Structure Guide

## Overview

This is a React + TypeScript project called "Who Knows U" - a WhatsApp chat opener tool that allows users to send messages without adding contacts.

## Main Entry Points

- [App.tsx](mdc:src/App.tsx) - Main application component
- [main.tsx](mdc:src/main.tsx) - Application entry point with React 19 imports
- [index.html](mdc:index.html) - HTML entry point with PWA manifest and meta tags

## Project Structure

### Source Organization

- `src/components/` - React components
  - [Footer.tsx](mdc:src/components/Footer.tsx) - Footer with tech badges
  - [PhoneInput.tsx](mdc:src/components/PhoneInput.tsx) - Phone input with country selector
  - [CountrySelector.tsx](mdc:src/components/CountrySelector.tsx) - Country dropdown selector
- `src/icons/` - SVG icon components
  - [WhatsAppIcon.tsx](mdc:src/icons/WhatsAppIcon.tsx)
  - [GitHubStarIcon.tsx](mdc:src/icons/GitHubStarIcon.tsx)
  - [ChevronDownIcon.tsx](mdc:src/icons/ChevronDownIcon.tsx)
- `src/data מונ movable` - Static data and constants (e.g., [countries-phone.ts](mdc:src/data/countries-phone.ts))
- `src/utils/` - Utility functions (e.g., [validateNumberPhone.ts](mdc:src/utils/validateNumberPhone.ts))
- `src/types.d.ts` - Type definitions
- `src/index.css` - Global styles and Tailwind imports with animations

### Configuration Files

- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and scripts
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration with path aliases
- [vite.config.ts](mdc:vite.config.ts) - Vite build configuration with PWA plugin
- [.eslintrc.json](mdc:.eslintrc.json) - ESLint configuration
- [.prettierrc.json](mdc:.prettierrc.json) - Prettier configuration

### Key Features

- WhatsApp link generation for direct messaging
- Country phone code selector with lazy-loaded images
- Phone number validation
- Spanish language support (documentation and UI)
- Tailwind CSS v4 with @theme configuration
- Fontsource fonts (DynaPuff and Poppins)
- Self-hosted fonts for better privacy and performance
- PWA support with service workers
- React 19 with latest hooks and optimizations
- Lazy loading for performance
- Mobile-first responsive design

### Path Aliases

- Use `@/` prefix to import from `src/` directory (e.g., `@/components/Footer`)
- Configured in [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json)
